In this article, President Donald J. Trump proclaims November 2017 as National Adoption Month. He acknowledges the importance of adoption for American families and highlights the positive impact it has on the lives of both parents and children. The proclamation emphasizes the need to remove barriers to adoption so that more children can find their forever homes. Trump also emphasizes the importance of adopting older children, as they can still benefit from the love and support of a family. The proclamation encourages all Americans to observe National Adoption Month by helping children in need of a permanent home secure a brighter future.